# MAYA Pledge Manager - Design & Development Rules

## UI/UX Design Rules

### Homepage / Store
- Add to cart button should be full width, matching the container above
- No upgrade badges or "YOUR PLEDGE" badges on pledge tier cards
- Remove all upgrade-related UI on the homepage
- Founders of Neh card should NOT have red/accent border - use standard border
- If backer is logged in, show their owned pledge in hero section with "PURCHASED" tag
- Hero section shows "YOUR PLEDGE" label instead of "FEATURED PLEDGE" for logged-in backers

### Add-ons Section
- Grid should be 3 columns (3x2 layout for 6 items)
- Cards should have large 1:1 aspect ratio images
- Use uniform dark background (var(--void)) for image containers - NOT white
- Image should use object-fit: contain with padding inside the container
- Price and name should be stacked vertically, not side by side

### Cards & Components
- All cards use var(--matter) background with var(--border) border
- Hover state: border-color changes to var(--border-hover), subtle translateY(-2px)
- No colored borders unless explicitly required for specific state
- Consistent border-radius: 16px for cards, 12px for inner elements

### Colors
- Background: var(--void) for deepest background
- Cards: var(--matter) 
- Borders: var(--border), hover: var(--border-hover)
- Text: var(--text-main) for primary, var(--text-dim) for secondary
- Accent: var(--accent) - use sparingly, only for CTAs and important actions
- Success states: #22C55E (green)

### Typography
- Mono font (IBM Plex Mono) for: prices, labels, badges, technical text
- Inter font for: headings, body text, descriptions
- All caps + letter-spacing for small labels and badges

### Buttons
- .btn-add: Full width, transparent bg, border, uppercase mono text
- Hover: invert colors (white bg, dark text)
- Primary buttons (.btn-primary): accent color background

## Development Rules

### Database
- Primary identifier: identity_id (UUID) for backers
- Don't store sensitive data in plain text
- Use proper foreign key relationships

### Session
- Store identityId in session after authentication
- Session data: identityId, email, backerNumber, etc.

### API Responses
- Always return JSON
- Include success/error status
- Log errors server-side, return user-friendly messages

### File Organization
- Views in /views
- API routes in /routes
- Database models in /db/models
- Services in /services
- Static assets in /public
